  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Livelihoods through Cooperatives, Renewable Energy and Gender Empowerment in Burundi-ABS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The  overall objective of the  project   is to empower  women farmers and economic actors   financially, economically,  and socially using the  renewable energy.  For this outcome  that will  be  implanted by   ABS and COCOCA  ,the   project  will  specifically   intend to  empower  coffee farmers for  better linkage  to remunerative markets through  increasing quality of the Horamama Women Brand and investment in renewable-energy based assets.  Through this intended change,  the market for  women coffee  will be guaranteed  and   boost they income   from the promotion of local  sales, and  accelerate the Organic Certification process , promotion of the HORAMAMA Women Coffee Brand,  Capacity Building in Good Agronomic Practices and with women farmers as lead trainers and economic empowerment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project   has three main outcomes ,   empowering  women coffee farmers   for better link  to remunerative market through strengthened   cooperatives  and  increase Horamama brand, empowering  small-scale  women  palm oil  processors  through  the  use of flexi Biogas system, and  empowering  Marginalised   women and girls socially , economically  through creation of  Sunflower   cooperative  and  better access  to finance .   ABS  will   implement   the  first   outcome  with following activities :    Capacity building and training for 1,623 female coffee farmers and Enhancement of Organic Certification, Coaching support to COCOCA (umbrella organisation of the cooperatives), the coffee marketing union and CNAC (coffee farmers national confederation) to fully own and upscale the development of cooperatives, and Enabling access to finance for female coffee farmers through creation of renewable-based enterprises.</narrative>
  </description>
